# Day 25 - Git Merge Branches | 100 Days of DevOps

## 📌 Project Overview

Today's lab focused on one of Git's most important collaborative workflows: **branching and merging**.

Instead of making changes directly on the `master` branch, I created a feature branch, added new content, committed the changes, 
merged the branch back into `master`, and pushed both branches to the remote repository.

This workflow mirrors how software teams safely develop and release new features in production environments.

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- Git
- Linux
- Git Branching
- Git Merge
- Git Commit
- Git Remote (Origin)

---

## 📂 Lab Requirements

- Create a new branch named **datacenter** from `master`
- Copy `/tmp/index.html` into the repository
- Stage and commit the file
- Merge the `datacenter` branch into `master`
- Push both `master` and `datacenter` branches to the remote repository

---

## ⚙️ Commands Used

```bash
cd /usr/src/kodekloudrepos/beta

git checkout -b datacenter

cp /tmp/index.html .

git add index.html

git commit -m "Add datacenter index page"

git checkout master

git merge datacenter

git push origin master

git push origin datacenter
```

---

## 🏗️ Workflow

```
master
   │
   ├───────────────┐
   │               │
   ▼               │
