## 💡 Key Learnings

- Create feature branches from the main branch
- Keep production code isolated while developing
- Stage and commit changes correctly
- Merge branches using Git
- Push multiple branches to a remote repository
- Understand the standard Git Feature Branch Workflow used in professional DevOps teams

---

## 🌍 Real-World Relevance

Feature branches are used by nearly every software engineering team.

Instead of committing directly to production, developers create isolated branches for new features, bug fixes, or experiments. 
Once reviewed and tested, those changes are merged into the main branch and deployed.

This workflow enables safer collaboration, easier code reviews, and reduced deployment risks.

